describing is correct.

00:04:30.400 --> 00:04:33.730 align:middle line:84%
There's like a mean
variability trade-off

00:04:33.730 --> 00:04:38.260 align:middle line:84%
here, a downward-sloping
frontier,

00:04:38.260 --> 00:04:40.210 align:middle line:84%
if you want to think
about it that way.

00:04:40.210 --> 00:04:42.430 align:middle line:84%
As you move across
different projects

00:04:42.430 --> 00:04:45.580 align:middle line:84%
they may have higher
and higher means,

00:04:45.580 --> 00:04:49.130 align:middle line:84%
but they come with higher
and higher variance.

00:04:49.130 --> 00:04:50.305 align:middle line:90%
So there's a trade-off.

00:04:50.305 --> 00:04:53.330 align:middle line:90%


00:04:53.330 --> 00:04:55.140 align:middle line:84%
And since households
are risk-averse,

00:04:55.140 --> 00:04:57.900 align:middle line:90%
they don't like the variance.

00:04:57.900 --> 00:04:59.225 align:middle line:90%
So they pay attention to that.

00:04:59.225 --> 00:05:02.550 align:middle line:90%


00:05:02.550 --> 00:05:04.340 align:middle line:90%
And you said this also.

00:05:04.340 --> 00:05:08.090 align:middle line:84%
You could have two technologies
with the same mean return--

00:05:08.090 --> 00:05:10.200 align:middle line:84%
one with a higher variance
than the other one,

00:05:10.200 --> 00:05:13.400 align:middle line:84%
and they would never do
the higher variability one

00:05:13.400 --> 00:05:16.270 align:middle line:84%
because then there's
no trade-off.

00:05:16.270 --> 00:05:18.580 align:middle line:84%
Since they get the same
mean but higher risk,

00:05:18.580 --> 00:05:21.010 align:middle line:90%
they wouldn't choose that.

00:05:21.010 --> 00:05:23.920 align:middle line:84%
There is a
diversification aspect

00:05:23.920 --> 00:05:28.480 align:middle line:84%
that we featured quite a
bit in terms of land plots

00:05:28.480 --> 00:05:31.300 align:middle line:84%
and how they want to
diversify, or in village India

00:05:31.300 --> 00:05:34.870 align:middle line:84%
over crops and income
sources and so on.

00:05:34.870 --> 00:05:38.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's kind of
captured here in a new way,

00:05:38.410 --> 00:05:40.120 align:middle line:90%
but it is in here.

00:05:40.120 --> 00:05:47.200 align:middle line:84%
Namely, a guess of
what technologies

00:05:47.200 --> 00:05:52.540 align:middle line:84%
