You're short, so you
withdraw, et cetera.

00:50:39.440 --> 00:50:41.210 align:middle line:84%
But when-- you
can't see much here,

00:50:41.210 --> 00:50:43.550 align:middle line:84%
but when you integrate
it out and look

00:50:43.550 --> 00:50:45.680 align:middle line:84%
at the consequence
for the levels

00:50:45.680 --> 00:50:50.120 align:middle line:84%
using this flow equation,
then you can see what

00:50:50.120 --> 00:50:51.942 align:middle line:90%
their stocks are.

00:50:51.942 --> 00:50:53.150 align:middle line:90%
It looks like a lot of money.

00:50:53.150 --> 00:50:56.150 align:middle line:90%
It is going to be unbelievable--

00:50:56.150 --> 00:50:58.010 align:middle line:84%
unbelievable in
the sense of three

00:50:58.010 --> 00:51:01.650 align:middle line:84%
years research running to try
to understand this pattern.

00:51:01.650 --> 00:51:03.950 align:middle line:84%
So how much money does
a typical household

00:51:03.950 --> 00:51:07.370 align:middle line:84%
have-- currency, paper,
squirreled away in the house?

00:51:07.370 --> 00:51:11.180 align:middle line:84%
In the rural villages
that we were looking at,

00:51:11.180 --> 00:51:15.050 align:middle line:84%
roughly 32 months
worth of consumption.

00:51:15.050 --> 00:51:16.670 align:middle line:90%
What's in your wallet?

00:51:16.670 --> 00:51:18.800 align:middle line:90%
You're going to say credit card.

00:51:18.800 --> 00:51:20.540 align:middle line:84%
These guys-- it's
not in a wallet.

00:51:20.540 --> 00:51:23.810 align:middle line:84%
It's in the house or
hidden in the backyard.

00:51:23.810 --> 00:51:27.800 align:middle line:84%
Almost three years worth
of expenditures in cash--

00:51:27.800 --> 00:51:29.360 align:middle line:90%
cash equivalent consumption.

00:51:29.360 --> 00:51:32.450 align:middle line:84%
We measure the consumption
for each household,

00:51:32.450 --> 00:51:34.160 align:middle line:84%
and we see how much
